## LSP diagnostics
- Ran `lsp_diagnostics` on every modified backend/frontend source and regression test file.
- Frontend changed files were clean except existing AntD deprecated prop hints in untouched surrounding page code (`headStyle`, `destroyOnClose`, `bodyStyle`).
- Backend diagnostics remain dominated by the known local environment noise already tracked in notepads: unresolved `fastapi`/`sqlalchemy`/`pydantic`/`pytest`, implicit `app.*` imports, and broad SQLAlchemy unknown-member reports. Runtime pytest and compile smoke passed.
